race.comment: It's hard to knock the form of MISSILE THUNDER (1) who has three wins and a second from his past four starts with Guernier being in the irons on all four occasions. Again gets the benefit of her 3kg claim and another strong showing would not surprise. TYCOON BEAU (5) has only missed a drum once in six spins around this circuit and has won when first-up before. Makes plenty of appeal. LIDDER VALLEY (2) is drawn to get all the favours from the inside alley and has saluted two from four when fresh. Top-three candidate. MOLONGLE SURPRISE (3) saves his best form for this course and distance with six wins and six placings from 14 attempts. Expect an improved showing. MIDAS STAR (6) grows a leg for hoop Teh who has three wins from as many steers. Capable of bringing up the hat-trick here.
